        <section name="Introduction">

            The Java Lattice Based Cryptography Library (jLBC) is a free Java library
            (released under the GNU Lesser General Public License)
            that performs the mathematical operations underlying lattice-based cryptosystems.

            jLBC consists of the following two core modules:
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green">jlbc-api</font>
                    :
                    the Application Program Interfaces (API).
                </li>

                <li>
                    <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green">jlbc-plaf</font>
                    :
                    the port implementation of the API.
                </li>
            </ul>
            and the following support modules:
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green">jlbc-crypto</font>
                    :
                    the implementation of some lattice based crypto-systems.
                    Have a look
                    <a href="./schemes/schemes.html">here</a>
                    to start.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

